Rating: 3
This is really good, but DO NOT cook the collard leaves for 15 minutes. It's too long if you still hope to roll these into "cigars." I think 10 minutes ought to do it. The recipe instructs you to remove the tough center rib anyway. I was unable to make the cigars after cooking the leaves for 15 minutes, and although I was able to assemble a kind of collard green casserole with the ingredients, I would like to serve these as rolls as intended.

